{"article_id":"CEjP2fEvkVEuq8Ua","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The April unemployment report suggests","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"that the economy is slowly recovering .","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"Jobs report tempers worries","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"A better than expected jobs report","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"released Friday","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"will most likely soothe worries","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"that the economy has entered a \" spring swoon , \"","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"but it continued to show","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"that the pace of economic growth remains too slow","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"to put a big dent in the unemployment number .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"The economy added 165,000 jobs in April","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"while unemployment dropped modestly to 7.5 percent ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"the Labor Department reported .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"The number beat expectations","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"with analysts estimating","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"that the economy added 145,000 jobs last month ,","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"according to a Reuters survey of economists .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"\" All things considered ,","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"165,000 isn ' t the biggest monthly gain in payrolls","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"you ' ll ever see ,","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"but it ' s enough","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"to assuage concerns","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"that the economy had stalled again , \"","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"Paul Ashworth , chief U.S. economist for Capital Economics , said in a statement .","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"The report contained good news about job growth in recent months .","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"The number of jobs","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"added for March","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"was revised upward from 88,000 to 138,000","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"and February figures were also revised up from 268,000 to 332,000 .","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"Friday ' s jobs numbers are certain to fuel ongoing concerns about the economic impact of across-the-board spending cuts","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"known as the sequester .","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"The cuts went into effect March 1","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"and the nonpartisan Congressional Budget Office has projected","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"they could lead to 750,000 fewer jobs this year","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"and scale back economic growth by 0.6 percent .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"\" Now is not the time","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"for Washington to impose self-inflicted wounds on the economy , \"","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"Chairman of the White House Council of Economic Advisers Alan Krueger said in a statement .","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"\" The Administration continues to urge Congress to replace the sequester with balanced deficit reduction ,","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"while working to put in place measures","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"to create middle-class jobs ,","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"such as by rebuilding our roads and bridges","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"and promoting American manufacturing . \"","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"Both Democrats and Republicans have derided the blunt nature of the sequester cuts ,","depth":3},{"id":44,"text":"which do not allow agencies to pick and choose where they can slash their budgets .","depth":3},{"id":45,"text":"But other than a recent effort","depth":5},{"id":46,"text":"to make sure the sequester did not lead to flight delays ,","depth":5},{"id":47,"text":"there is little evidence","depth":4},{"id":48,"text":"there will be a deal","depth":4},{"id":49,"text":"to delay or greatly alter the way","depth":5},{"id":50,"text":"the cuts are being implemented .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":101,"left":93,"right":100,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":93,"left":53,"right":92,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":53,"left":52,"right":2,"relation":"